Let us=
 get back to the specific example mentioned below. Suppose I want to do hom=
am regularly and my room mate may not like it. From the words uttered by my=
 room mate (as heard by my ears) and the facial expressions shown (as seen =
by my eyes), possibly on several occasions, I can come to a limited objecti=
ve understanding of his attitude and thinking. I may know that he is not pl=
eased. Forming a more complete picture of what he thinks, wants and why, is=
 akin to connecting dots to make a nice picture. One can paint a whole rang=
e of possible pictures within what one knows objectively. But, one's condit=
ioning pushes one to pick a few possibilities out of those. We do that all =
the time without being conscious of it.
=C2=A0
Suppose I am conditioned to =
be proud of the religious work I do and to think that some evil forces may =
stop me in my good work. The desire to do homam itself is not a problem, bu=
t this undesirable conditioning can be a problem. When someone shows disple=
asure at my doing homam in the room, my conditioning may push some wrong bu=
ttons in me (!) and trigger resentment. A negative character with a lot of =
friction with me is propped up in my internal world! My thoughts, words and=
 actions will project (physically and also subtly) that character and its f=
riction with me, onto the external world through resonance. The other perso=
n may become even more negative than before, as a result of resonance with =
my internal world. As both parties act as slaves of their conditioning and =
act without self-control, things can snowball and there can be an environme=
nt of great resentment and friction.
=C2=A0
This is kind of like moviemaker=
s depicting violence and gore excessively, saying that they are only reflec=
ting what is happening in society, while society being influenced by movies=
 and engaging in even more violence and then moviemakers pushing the envelo=
pe further, and so on.
=C2=A0
Suppose I am devoid of much negative conditio=
ning and all I want is to do homam if possible. When someone shows displeas=
ure, that will then not press any wrong buttons in me and trigger any resen=
tment. I will note the fact that they have some displeasure. Because my vis=
ion is not clouded with conditioning (to be proud of my work and look at pe=
ople creating obstacles as evil people), I may be able to understand their =
perspective better. On the balance, I may still choose to go ahead and do h=
omam, but without much resentment in my mind. The character propped up in m=
y mind may not be a very negative one and not have much friction with me. I=
 may love this character from my internal world, feel compassionate about i=
t, understand its motivations and yet do my homam. Then my thoughts, words =
and actions will project (physically and also subtly) that nice character a=
nd my love for it, onto the external world through resonance. Even if the o=
ther person is more
 negative than I realized, influence of (resonance with=
) my internal world will eventually change him for better. (It will atleast=
 not make him worse!!)
