 wife in one's inner world needs to be transformed. One can try to put ones=
elf in the shoes of wife and try to figure out the picture is from her side=
. Most people in this world are not 100% terrible. They are an amalgam of g=
ood and bad. Perhaps one's wife actually loves one and one's words conveyed=
 to her that he is not happy and her sub-conscious disappointment at not be=
ing to make husband happy showed up externally as an outburst. So many such=
 possibilities exist. People's external actions don't always reflect the de=
epest motivations. Attachments make people act strangely. Some people who f=
eel a deep attachment to us may act harsh with us.
=C2=A0
If one can put on=
eself in the shoes of wife and come up with a more compassionate explanatio=
n of her behavior and attribute as positive motivations to her behavior as =
possible, then one's notions about the character of wife in the inner world=
 will improve. Then one may be able to behave nicely without suppressing an=
y feelings! This is more sustainable in the long-term. As the character of =
wife in the inner world becomes nicer and nicer, it will reflect in one's e=
xternal behavior with the corresponding person in the external world. This =
will eventually impact the thinking of wife (in external world) and reflect=
 in her behavior with one.
=C2=A0
Through one's actions and the other perso=
n's actions, slowly the discrepancies between a character in one's inner wo=
rld and one's outer world come down and the two characters come close to ea=
ch other. So you transform the outer world character by transforming the in=
ner world character. This is really the only way you can control the extern=
al world on a sustainable basis.
